# Project-Specific Rules

This file is automatically generated for you to add repository-specific rules, conventions, and guidelines that are unique to your project.

## How to Use This File

Add any project-specific rules here, such as:
- Custom naming conventions
- Project-specific architectural patterns
- Team agreements and coding standards
- Domain-specific terminology and concepts
- Integration patterns with external services
- Deployment and environment-specific guidelines

## Example Rules

You can document things like:
- "Use `UserEntity` suffix for all database models"
- "All API endpoints must include rate limiting"
- "Feature flags are managed through LaunchDarkly"
- "Authentication uses Auth0 with custom claims"

## Tips

- Keep this file updated as your project evolves
